comment.text: For one the food is great. I had the yellow tail appetizer (the great wave?) solid 8/10. Would order again. And then I got the tempura roll (salmon and yellowtail?) that was nice 7/10 and the drink was great the lychee pearl 9/10. I would give this place a higher rating but I was by myself sat at the bar and the bartenders took like 10 minutes to even look in my direction and when the guy did finally see me he forgot to key in my order. So it did take a hot minute for me to even get a water. Other than that I think the restaurant itself is busy. I had a reservation, probably best to stick with a reservation. Also they add a 18% gratuity for parties under 4 so keep that in mind as well. The actual venue itself if pretty nice. If I come back it will probably be as a date. The dress code is also all over the place as well.

I'm shocked at the 4.2-star rating of this place because my experience was outstanding. From the delicious King Crab Fried Rice, which lived up to its social media hype, to the excellent service, and beautiful decor, this restaurant exceeded our expectations. There were so many tempting entrees, like the Drunken Man Spaghetti and Egg Crepe Pad-Thai Lobster, but I had my heart set on King Crab Fried Rice. It had a generous portion of crab fried rice and the crab cluster was huge. It also came with a Cajun Butter that I didn't think was necessary, and kind of fought with the seasoning already on the crab, but it was delicious nonetheless. My boyfriend selected the braised short rib that came with a side of mashed potatoes and carrots. He enjoyed his meal and I enjoyed the bite I tasted.  For dessert, I chose the Thai mousse cheesecake which surprised me with its creamy texture and perfect balance of sweetness.

The ambiance of the restaurant, adorned with captivating Asian decor, adds to the dining experience, whether for an intimate meal or a gathering with friends. The service was great. Our waitress was very attentive. 

Without a doubt, I'll be returning!

We went for happy hour so it was fairly calm and the service was great! We had small dishes from the happy hour menu and cocktails as well. I would say overall they were 6/10. 

There were a total of 4 vegetarian dishes, so very little option but you can always ask them to alter. We had tofu fried rice and it was okay. Nothing exceptional. 

The place itself is pretty! Really aesthetically appealing and incorporated many cultural elements of a Thai restaurant. Parking is validated through license plate and the garage is behind their restaurant.

photos.caption: Fried Shrimp Skewer, Garlic Green Bean

comment.text:
Good date night spot

Ambience was nice, but the chill from the door opening repeatedly made the experience "cold."

Our server Kim was very nice. We had the mussels, calamari, Tom Yum, and Lobster Roll.

The drinks were the Geisha, Lychee Pearl, Thai Tini, and Basil Margaritas.

Everything was nice. Would come again.

This was a hit and i will be back!!!! We were looking for a spot to take my mom and aunt for their birthdays. Found this on Yelp and after looking at reviews made a reservation. They did not disappoint. They have parking behind the building which is great. Free for the first three hours. Our server was very helpful and made sure we had everything we needed. The food!!!! When I say everything was good, I mean that!  I had the drunken man spaghetti which i ended up eating it all when I got home. I did try my aunts snapper and I am going back for that. Best one I have had in awhile. The decor is super cute and intimate. Smaller than I expected but it doesn't feel overwhelming. This place is absolutely worth a try.
Again, the food was amazing! I came tonight with my sisters. Kennedy was our server and everything we consumed was delicious. We will definitely be back very soon!

OKAYYYYY! The hype is REAL!

Osha must be in my top three sushi spots here in Atlanta.

This isn't just food but art! The sushi is plated in which a unique way and the the drinks are creative. Giving you an experience, you won't forget! 

The restaurant itself is beautiful. It's very tranquil yet lively. You feel completely immersed in culture, it's the small details you must pay attention to. They do play music but it kind of blends with the noise of the restaurant so you aren't struggling to hear someone speak. 

I've been to Osha on several different occasions; brunch, lunch, date night, work event and a girl's day out. This restaurant embodies all those vibes.

The service here is top tier. Like you're never going to be looking for your server. Food always comes out fresh and hot. The hostess always tries to seat you as soon as possible if you don't have reservations. The waitstaff don't mind explaining the menu and offering suggestions. 

Let's get into the eats. The food, man the FOOD! I have yet to be disappointed. Some of my favorites are the Crab Fried Rice, Seafood Boil, Shrimp Tempura, Crispy Red Snapper, Crab Cakes, The P.E.I Mussels, The King of the Sea, and The Lobster Roll.

**If you don't see any sushi you like on the menu, you can tell them what you want, and they will make it. It's an Osha hack. Lol. **


The parking is validated so don't forget to grab your tag number on the way in!

Wanted to love this place based off of the Instagram videos and reviews but..... the inside looked very different than the videos very misleading. The food sadly was less than desirable we've had way better authentic Thai food back home in NY. The crab fried rice was way too messy, too much salt. My son had the beef dish while
Very tender again way too much sauce that took away from the flavors of the meat and the majority of the meat was FAT. I had the Pad Thai noodles way too rubbery and salty and the drinks were also mediocre. I wouldn't go back but wouldn't discourage anyone from giving them a try.
Osha was really good. The food was delicious, flavorful, great portions, great service, and the ambiance was cute. I would definitely recommend trying them and I would certainly go again.

Lovely restaurant that was recommended to me by a local! There's plenty of space both inside and out, and the interior is both uniquely and ornately decorated. They validate parking for you, and on the weekends they serve brunch and bottomless mimosas.

I wish they had more non-alcoholic beverage options, but Thai tea was available and delicious too. Their brunch menu consists of traditional breakfast dishes with a flare of seafood. The waffles were impressive in size, but I thought their regular menu had better food options. Gyozas are great to share and the King of the Sea was beautiful in presentation! The roll itself was pretty good, though the side of soft shell crab tempura was not my favorite. 

I thought the dishes were a bit overpriced but had a pleasant experience overall! Server was nice enough to help split the bill among our table of 4.

photos.caption: Honey maple hot chicken (left), lobster waffle (right)
King of the Sea - castle was bigger than my face!

comment.text:
Drinks are great!!!! Food, unfortunately I was not very impressed with my sushi selection. The complimentary parking is in the back, but you get validated with no ticket inside the restaurant. 
Drinks are $10 with happy hour and appetizers are $7. I hope next time the food is better, but at least I know the cocktails will be amazing!

photos.caption: Me with one of my ladies on the outside patio- parking in the back.

comment.text:
This place is very cute. I came solo and sat at the bar. The food is good but the reason for 3 stars has more to do with the menu. I didn't see too many options that appealed to me and some things were a bit pricey. Otherwise I don't have any other complaints.

I ordered the dumplings and drunken spaghetti which were good. I also enjoyed the Lychee Pearl. 

I might give this place another and try something different - I want to try the Butterfly Kiss.

I love OSHA. The food never disappoints.

I was disappointed to find that they changed my favorite dish which was the dinner version of steak frites with these 2 really delicious sauces. But i got over it.,

The chicken and waffles was delicious. Perfectly cooked waffle with really yummy chicken. 5 star

Calamari- perfect. Crispy and well seasoned 5 star 

Crab fried rice -  the rice was good but it wasn't the kind of crab I am used to and it tasted a little fake. I wound up pushing the crab off of my rice. 4 star 

Overall great experience as always

photos.caption: Amazing ! Served with a sauce for the fries and steak .. sooo good

comment.text: The sushi was delicious and as well as the garlic green beans. I tried to braised short rib. It was very tender but it was a unique taste to it. Very different than what I'm use to. The service was decent. The ambiance was very nice.

I LOVE this restaurant. The ambience is great for a date night or birthday dinner. I've had both here. It's beautiful decor and even their food presentation is its an artwork.

The servers are always attentive and will share their recommendations. I don't think you can go wrong with trying anything on the menu. 

Some of my favorite dishes are: salmon tartare, the great wave, crispy red snapper, king fried rice and Van Gogh

photos.caption: Delicious cocktails in bird glass! Very tasty & strong

comment.text:
Parking; there's a parking garage in the back of the building that offers free validation for patrons. 

Ambiance:  The atmosphere is casual but it's very trendy and decorated with memorabilia from different parts of Asian culture.

Service: we came in a weekend night so it was a bit busy but the hostess and server were both friendly. 

Food: the most important part of any restaurant. Here, osha falls short in my opinion. The presentation is absolutely on point, but the actual quality of the food is lacking. The flavors were not there and at times the rolls kind of tasted like... nothing. Side note: it's a pretty gimmick to have a little statue with each roll order but after ordering a bunch our table felt like the lost city of Atlantis. 

It's a neat and trendy sushi place with great presentation but for the price the rolls were lacking in quality and flavor.

photos.caption: The Starry night (did not have much flavor)

comment.text:
This place sets the bar as to what it means to give a place a 5 star rating! 

I just assumed this place would be like all other Thai restaurants but was I totally wrong! This upscale place as a vibe. Not necessarily Thai vibe but just a vibe. Walking in the decor is very modern and intentional. You know how some restaurants just have "stuff" with no real rhyme or reason? This place has rhyme and reason! 

The menu...my goodness the menu the menu. Such great choices. Some traditional Thai and then Thai with flavor. I opted for lobster and waffle. That's right lobster. It was amazing! I also had Thai tea also very good. We had a table of 6 and the service didn't lack one bit. I'm such a fan of this place I tell all my friends who visit to go! Oh and bonus- they valet your parking!!

Not sure why this place has 4.2 star review. Came here for dinner during happy hour, food was decent, ambiance was good, service is ok. Nothing really stood out to me and cocktail taste ok. Came here the other night with my husband and baby, was shocked to see they charged us 18% on gratuity. I don't remember the last time a restaurant did that for just 2 ppl

Walk in and I'm greeted right away... plus! Look around and the restaurant is decorated beautifully, it went with the Thai theme. I'm immediately 
taken to my seat, where my party is waiting and she was already having a drinking and sushi. I ended up ordering the same drink, can't remember the name but it was amazing and I ordered the same sushi, it was just as amazing and would order them both again. My entree was sorry to say just ok, it wasn't bad just not to my liking. I would go back for sure and I definitely recommend everyone give them a try at least once. I wish I could remember our waiters name because he was great!!

Went for a friend's birthday and I was expecting more honestly. On tiktok it looks bigger but it's really small. Calamari was just okay, it was served with some sweet chili sauce. The katsu curry was really good & had a little kick to it. Our waiter was good, he gave great sugges

Very yummy sushi! Recently visited to celebrate my birthday. They have a parking deck in the back, as you enter the restaurant you can validate your parking with your license plate number. The ambiance of the restaurant is super pretty. My partner and I ordered 2 rolls to start, then ordered more. Ended up ordering 4 total: Van Gogh, impression sunshine, Siam Ruby, and the Yayoi. My favorite was the Van Gogh. Their alcoholic drinks looked very good, but opted to just drink water. They brought out a complimentary slice of cheesecake for dessert to celebrate the birthday. Overall good experience.
Amazing sushi and ambience! Although I wish parking was validated, it didn't take away from the service and food. I will definitely be returning!
The food was amazing and the ambiance was nice. We had a great server for a party of 15. Everything was so good. Parking was a huge parking garage and they validated.

My boyfriend's cousin came into town for a visit and we came to eat here, it was delicious! They loved the food here, and it was an amazing experience. It's very cute inside with a mellow ambiance, and they play good music too. Kim was our server and she was lovely. Side note, they do apply an 18% gratuity to each check, but Kim was so great that I tipped on top of the gratuity! I would come here again with my girls to drink more, but everything was fantastic, from the food, to the drinks, to the service! Loveee!

photos.caption: Crispy Whole Red Snapper and Seared filet of Salmon!

comment.text: I decided to give OSHA another try and it is still a restaurant I wouldn't necessarily recommend. They did change the menu but the food/price ratio is just not worth it. The drinks on the other hand will give this place 5 stars - maybe it was a plan "have everyone drink and they won't really care about the food!" The ambiance is cute and sexy .... We ordered the shrimp skewers and calamari - appetizers were fresh and hot and better than the main entrees. I ordered the king of the sea roll for my main course and it was just as good as the rolls at Publix.

Came here for a friends birthday dinner on Saturday at 7pm! It was not crowded at all! The atmosphere was very nice, but cozy. The decor was cute & Thai themed. Cute aesthetic. The plating & drinks were cute too.! 

Parking was very efficient. There is a designated parking garage adjacent to the building, & Osha validates your parking for 3 hrs. Do not pay at the machine in the garage, just take a note of your tag & they will validate it in the restaurant! 

Our server Alexandra was very sweet & knowledgable of the menu. She was attentive & accommodating. We really enjoyed her service.

Food was pretty good! Portions on the entree's were good. Love that they allow meat substitutions in their entrees. 
I had the seafood pasta, chicken dumplings, deep down sushi, & Thai tea. 
Food was actually quite delightful. I enjoyed the pasta. It's more of a sweet curry. Sushi was a hint bit salty, but good. Crab cakes were on the smaller side, but tasty. 

They brought out a complimentary dessert for the birthday gal, & that was a nice touch. 
We enjoyed our time here.! 
Overall, I'd probably return.

I met a friend here for Sunday brunch. It was great. The customer service was good. My food was great! I had the crispy Brussels sprouts with goat cheese and chicken skewers. They were both amazing. The goat cheese had a creaminess that elevated the flavor of the Brussels sprouts. The skewers came with a side of peanut sauce. Yum! I'll definitely be back. My friend had the shrimp skewers and Brussels sprouts and enjoyed them both. Parking was easy. You can get it validated by giving them your license plate number inside the restaurant. Give them a try!

photos.caption: Chicken Skewer and Crispy Brussels Sprouts

comment.text: Good dinner here last week with a friend. I love that they have a parking deck right next to it so that it's easy to park. When you enter, just put your license plate into the iPad at the hostess stand and you will be good to go. The cocktails here are so fun! They also have a great food menu. I got the Mona Lisa roll and loved it!

I just want to say this is one of the best presentations they do for sushi I have seen and loved how everything was presented. My sushi was so fresh and delicious and ordered a drink which was super cute and good. My friends also ordered some sushi and we all got different ones and tried each others and love it !! Service was also great and the experience was all I asked for ! It is a little pricy but worth the price, my favorite dish was the coconut soup.

This is honestly the best Thai food I've had, and I've had a lot of it! The drinks, food, and atmosphere all 10/10. I give the service a 9/10, only bc it took them quite some time to initially come to the table. This is definitely a new entry on "my spot" list. 

Even though I was toasting alone with my glass of H2O, my girls drinks not only presented well, but passed the test!

All three of us were happy with our food selections & apps: sushi, crab cakes, calamari, salt & pepper shrimp, drunken spaghetti, & fried rice.

OSHA is always a a wonderful time! You can park in the garage around the corner and validate it for free for 3 hours, WIN!

You MUST make a reservation, especially on the weekend. Like don't even try it and waste your time. This is a super vibey cute date night or girls night out spot so walking in is probably only cool for the bar early in the evening. They tag team service here so there's always someone close by refilling your drink or getting you an app, so you know that means the gratuity is already included in the bill... it's totally worth it tho so whatevs.

Every single thing we ate was fabulous as always, but The Great Wave remains the singular most delicious bite I've had in Atlanta. Don't miss this spot!!

photos.caption: The Starry night is always a fave!!
Mona Lisa, this was great too!
A butterfly kiss, their version of a French 75

comment.text:
This is some of the best Thai food I've ever had. I feel like as delicious and consistent the food is and how great a location they're in...they're never overly crowded when I visit. The ambience in the restaurant is really calming and beautiful, day or night. The music is never loud, the staff never seem stressed, and it's always calming to me because of how it's decorated. Their reservation system is straightforward and they validate parking as well.

Bottomless Mimosas - they have i think 4-5 different juices for the mimosas and our server kept our glasses full.
Gyoza - always a consistent hit
Butter Shrimp Tempura - these shrimp sticks are fried to perfection, light and crisp on the outside.
Calamari - Thai restaurants have the best calamari. Idk what magic it is, but it's just true.
Lobster Tail & Waffle - Listen, Linda. If you like Lobster, get this. The waffle is lightly sweet, so goes really well if you like to eat the lobster meat and waffle in the same bite. Highly recommend!
King Lobster roll (i think) - this role is large and even comes with shrimp tempura on the side.
DaVinci roll - my friend really enjoyed this! I believe it has smoked salmon on it.
Salt & Pepper Shrimp

I always have a great time and highly recommend it!

Also, because we were there really close to brunch ending and the restaurant closing, we saw the staff setting up for a family-style meal to eat. How lovely - loved that!

We came for dinner. We had to email to make reservations since we had a party of more than 4. They accommodated us by sending a contract and with a minimum of $400. The restaurant is small and intimate so it makes sense that they do it like that. Parking is in a garage they will validate it for 3 hours. Don't make the mistake I did and forget to give them your license plates numbers in the beginning. (My car was fine ) They will not seat you until your party has arrived. 

For drinks, they have cute cocktails- I had the lychee pearl and champagne. For appetizers, we had  Brussels sprouts with goat cheese, steamed dumplings, fried dumplings, calamari, golden triangle and sleeping Venus rolls. My favorite were the Brussels sprouts. Everything was really tasty. 

For entrees we had the King crab fried rice, parpadelle seafood pasta, ribeye, Lobster pad Thai, Drunken noodle. Everyone's food tasted great. 

We were celebrating a birthday. They brought us a slice of cheesecake with a candle.

Service was great. I can't wait to come back for brunch for bottomless mimosas.

No question this was the most beautifully prepared sushi that I have ever had. The drinks were lovely and equally as pretty. I believe I got the Lychee Pearl and I did really like it but it needed a bit more citrus to round it out.

As for the rolls, we shared the Hangover and (I think) Picasso. Both very good but not the best rolls I've ever had, especially for the price. That said, the presentation really did make it entirely worth it. 

Based almost entirely on presentation, I would definitely return to Osha and recommend it to others!

Beautiful seating. Beautiful display of some really good food. My server was awesome, definitely had some great appetizer suggestions. Over all experience was amazing! This was 3rd time going to Osha and they have yet to miss a note

Osha is truly an experience! Every food item and drink suggestion was on point. It exceeded my expectations and truly provided an amazing dining experience. From the decor to the detailed presentation of each drink and food entree and appetizer to the awesome staff. It was amazing. I'll definitely go back.

There is a shared parking garage. It does get crowded. I would suggest arriving early to give yourself time to possibly wait for spot. Parking is free. You walk out the garage around to the street entrance to Osha.

There's a beautiful Osha sign when you enter. Decor at entrance makes for great photos. Suggest making a reservation for sure at least a week in advance. It gers crowded as the night goes on.

We were seated immediately. The server came over within minutes. I was looking at the decor, just beautiful. He suggested the green beans, and I wanted calamari. The way he described the green beans made it a must. They were sooo good. Try them when you visit.

Drinks we went with Geisha and Apple Pie Old Fashioned. Both drinks came out on interesting drink stands. The Geisha was really good. I ended up having two. The flavor profile was on point. 

For entrees, we ordered the Salt and pepper shrimp with side of fried rice and Special fish entree with side of rice. I ordered my son the Golden fish and chips to go. My fish was so delicious and flavorful. I ate every bite. I ate all my food. Lol. Perfect portion sizes. My friend shrimp was good too. We had zero complaints. We debated ordering more green beans to go.

It was a bit smaller than I thought. However, it's longer not as wide. The restaurant is beautiful. It was a great experience. I did spend think $100 solo. However, I got my money's worth.

photos.caption: Special of Day w fried rice

comment.text:
Beautiful decor! Small space, but the ambiance was soothing. Cute date night or friend date. Creative cocktails and fun staff! 
Reservation is definitely recommended. Parking was a little confusing for me, but they validate for you in the restaurant. 
Two of my friends and I went for dinner and ordered a table full of food and shared. Everything was pretty delicious, except for the crab cakes. Which they should call crab bites. They tasted more like stuffing, than crab cakes. 
Calamari wasn't over cooked so good, muscles had a delicious sauce on them, gyoza was delicious and fresh, salt and pepper shrimp was so good and fresh, king crab fried rice and crab legs was amazing, and my cocktails was ON POINT!!! No disappointment with all of that food! I can't wait to go back and try other things!!

Food AMAZING. Service was ok, nothing bad. 
Ambiance is cool. Def a date night or dinner before event type of spot. Kind of on the pricey side, but worth it. 10/10 i just suggested this place to someone the other day.
Place is cute for the vibes but the food isn't the best and it is pricey for the the amount you get

Whewwwwww let's talk about this Pappardelle Seafood  this right here had me weak in the knees. Lol the sweet spicy balance (you can get it without the spice as well) the curry, calamari, shrimp, mussels! 10/10! 

We also had the Mango Sake and it was delicious as well ! 

The calamari  crunchy balance, but soggy or salty at all! Just perfect! 
Please kiss the chef for me! 

The service was amazing
The ambiance is perfect...the music isn't too loud but you can still vibe and enjoy your food. The place isn't crowded at all and guess what else...THEY VALIDATE YOUR PARKING. You don't even have to go to the machine. Take a picture of your license plate and they'll handle the rest! 

The only annoying part was 18% gratuity was already added in. It always makes me feel weird if I don't leave a tip when I see gratuity already added but our waitress deserved the extra so we paid her more with no grief! 


I loved my experience and I really can't wait to go back ! 
I want this place to do well but ima cry if they get packed out

photos.caption: The BUK tang! So good. It's really refreshing, not made too strong but you'll definitely enjoy the Balance it has! 10/10 for sure!

comment.text:
The ambiance of this place is really nice. I came here for lunch and they have lunch specials deals which are pretty good. 

I ordered the crab fired rice without the crab legs and it was okay. I thought the crab meat would be mixed within the rice but they just placed it on top. The crab meat was a bit salty but once you mix it with the rice it doesn't taste as bad because the rice as no salty lol. I wasn't a fan of the fried rice so I wouldn't get it again. 

The shrimp tempura app was pretty good. It wasn't covered with too much batter. 

The staff is very polite and nice. I experienced good costumer service here. 

I def would like to come back and try different things on the menu because their food is so unique here.

I went to Osha for my birthday dinner, the food was delish and great ambiance!
For starters we had the garlic green beans and chicken dumplings, both very tasty. We also ordered the most popular entrees ( I don't remember names lol) photos are attached. Drink selection- where's my Duck and Tiki Thai, both were great! Last but not least get the red velvet cake, so yummy! 
Please note there is ample parking located on side of building. Be sure to input your license plate number in the iPad located by the hostess stand, you'll get up to three hours complimentary parking.

photos.caption: Tiki Thai and Where's my duck

comment.text: I visited this restaurant with my girlfriend for a birthday. This was the specific group of friends was down for the food so we had a ball! We ordered almost every appetizer on the menu in the video I'm attaching with my review you'll see a table full of appetizers. My personal favorite was the muscles in the sauce that came with it  .  To DIE FOR - next up was the calamari  the sauce that came with it was a sweet chili sauce. I had a glass of Grigio, but others at the table ordered some of their specialty cocktails. I tasted most of them, and all the cocktails were very good. There was one drink that was a little strong, and I can't remember the name of it, but we did ask for some additional purée, and it made the drink sweeter for my friend. The atmosphere is very date night as far as ambience. There was a lot of couples and girl groups it gave grown and sexy. I didn't use the bathroom during our time there, so I can't state the cleanliness of that but the table service was very well. They didn't leave your table, cluttered, or covered or anything of the such.  I was just was super friendly and knowledgeable. I did taste some sushi. It was also really good. I cannot remember the name of the Roll. The menu is very fairly priced as well, it's not overly expensive. I really enjoyed my time and experience here and I would definitely come back for a date night.
I've been wanting to go here for a minute, and it met expectations! Drink and roll were delicious. The ambiance was cool too.
Met a friend here for lunch since we both have never been here. We loved the decor and vibe. Drinks were amazing and good as well. Parking however was a bit of a hassle but we'll definitely return!

Ok so the ambiance is nice , definitely expected more from looking at TikTok. MY food was good and drink was nice & strong . The service was good as well and they validate parking. My friend ordered the same roll as me but she had soup and I didn't . She ended up getting food poisoning from this place. So I guess if you're willing to take chance for the sushi go but I wouldn't order anything else

Good was good and our server was great but unfortunately the hostess was incredibly rude. Unable to make a small accommodation even though the restaurant was completely empty. We had one reservation of 4 and one of 2 and wanted to sit together, she explained she couldn't do that and didn't even ask or try. We understood so we asked to at least find 2 tables next to each other but that was also not possible. 
It's very hard to come back to a restaurant that doesn't appreciate the effort it is to spend $700 on one dinner for a regular Saturday, there are plenty of restaurants in Atlanta that would love our business.
The food and our server was very nice so we ended up having a nice dinner but will not be coming back.

photos.caption: The restaurant completely empty, there were plenty of options to accommodate our simple request.

comment.text:
Found a hair in my food their health rating needs to be lower. 

My hair was pulled back in a ponytail, and my hair is not curly like the hair found in my food was. 

Our unfriendly server was Asian, and after I mentioned the hair, he sent over a black server (who was not a manager) for whatever reason (because I'm also black?)

The other server let us know that the manager was going to take 15% off. Yes 15%. For a $12 lunch menu meal. 

This completely turned me off this place.

I loved loved this place. The sushi is the best I have tasted yet. Very very fresh ingredients and so yummy. The drinks I ordered were fabulous as well. The service was fast and my server was patient with us (I and my friends were indecisive). And the dumplings?? I could eat 15 of them! The ambiance was very engaging except for some customers that were really loud. I didn't give them a 5 star because of the NO APPLE PAY policy. That was very very inconvenient for me but was sorted. Thank God Chile. I will be back to try so much sushi

photos.caption: A cocktail with pomegranate in it. Don't know the name

comment.text:
Oh my goodness. This food is sooo good.  My friend got the Red snapper and I got the salmon.  Everything was so tasty.  The green beans were grilled maybe?? But the we're seasoned like I've never tasted. Moving forward whatever dish I get I will swap the veggies out for those green beans!!  it's a good amount of food.  As far as my salmon I probably would have gotten it done medium well but my friend ordered while I went to the restroom and she ordered it well done. While it was not melting in my mouth it was also not tough. It came with a nice sauce and white rice.  Now I generally don't eat white rice but in order to get all the sauce I had to put the rice in it.  The red snapper though..crispy and seasoned well. Its really the kind of dish you need to eat at home so you can really go to work!! 

Customer service was super. From the hostess to our server to whoever the gentleman was that we spoke with before leaving everyone was great!!  I made a reservation but my event went long and we were late..still within the 15 minute grace period so we were seated immediately. I heard them tell someone on the phone it was an hour wait.  I can't wait to go back. They have brunch on the weekends. Make sure you remember your tag number..that's how they validate your parking.
